# Document Processing Workflows

## Document Lifecycle for KMRL Operations

### 1. Ingestion Stage
**Supported Formats**: PDF, DOCX, images (PNG, JPG), plain text
**Sources**: Email attachments, Maximo exports, SharePoint, WhatsApp PDFs, scanned documents

**Processing Pipeline**:
- Format detection and validation
- Text extraction with OCR for images
- Bilingual content recognition (English/Malayalam)
- Metadata extraction (creation date, author, etc.)

### 2. Analysis Stage
**AI Processing Components**:
- **Document Classification**: Categorize by type (engineering drawings, maintenance cards, regulatory bulletins)
- **Key Information Extraction**: Parse structured data (invoice amounts, dates, reference numbers)
- **Entity Recognition**: Identify personnel names, equipment IDs, station references
- **Content Summarization**: Generate executive summaries for lengthy documents

### 3. Routing & Distribution
**Smart Routing Logic**:
- **Department Mapping**: Route based on content analysis
  - Engineering drawings → Rolling-stock Engineers
  - Safety bulletins → Station Controllers
  - Vendor invoices → Finance Officers
  - Policy updates → HR Teams
- **Priority Classification**: Flag urgent/time-sensitive documents
- **Compliance Tagging**: Mark regulatory documents for tracking

### 4. Search & Discovery
**Multi-modal Search**:
- **Text Search**: Full-text search across extracted content
- **Semantic Search**: Vector-based similarity matching
- **Metadata Filters**: Department, date range, document type
- **Visual Search**: Image content recognition for technical drawings

## AI Model Integration

### Language Models
- **OpenAI GPT**: Document summarization and analysis
- **spaCy**: Named entity recognition and text processing
- **Custom Embeddings**: Domain-specific document similarity

### Performance Optimizations
- **Lazy Loading**: Models load only when needed ([backend/lazy_nlp.py](mdc:backend/lazy_nlp.py))
- **Caching**: Store processed results to avoid re-computation
- **Batch Processing**: Handle multiple documents efficiently

## Compliance & Security

### Regulatory Requirements
- **Commissioner of Metro Rail Safety**: Bulletin tracking and compliance monitoring
- **Ministry of Housing & Urban Affairs**: Policy document management
- **Audit Trails**: Complete document access and modification history

### Data Protection
- **PII Redaction**: Automatic removal of sensitive personal information
- **Access Controls**: Role-based document visibility
- **Retention Policies**: Automated archival based on document age/type

## Integration Points

### External Systems
- **Maximo**: Maintenance work order integration
- **SharePoint**: Document repository synchronization
- **Email Systems**: Automatic document ingestion from attachments
- **IoT/UNS**: Future integration with sensor data and condition monitoring